 when one takes a look at recent national and international studies on the situation of migrants in educational institutions, and in the transition to vocational education, which show the reduced prospects of success and the diverse disadvantages of people with migrant backgrounds. Anselm Böhmer discusses the multitude of corresponding empirical findings as well as the educational models which underlie them, and proposes concrete measures for breaking down institutional discrimination in the education system and for the advancement of the integration of refugees through educational processes.  afunded by Bundesinstitut für Berufsbildung (BIBB)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAdult educationzGermany. 0aImmigrantsxEducationzGermany. 0aRefugeesxEducationzGermany. 0aSocial integrationzGermany. 4aArbeitsmarkt. 4aAusbildung. 4aBildungschancen. 4aBildungsforschung. 4aDeutschland. 4aFlucht. 4aFlüchtlinge. 4aFlüchtlingsforschung. 4aIntegration. 4aMigration. 4aPädagogik. 7aEDUCATION / Organizations & Institutions.2bisacsh  aEducational Careers.  aEducational Research.  aFleeing.  aGermany.  aIntegration.  aLabour Market.  aMigration.  aPedagogy.  aRefugee Studies.  aRefugees.  aTraning.2 aBundesinstitut für Berufsbildung (BIBB)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2016z9783110485332oZDB-23-DSW08